class Spectrum:
    
    def __init__(self, allStar, dir_name):
        
        self.wav_lim1 = 15830
        self.wav_lim2 = 16400
        
        self.dir_name = dir_name
        self.stars = self.save_cols(allStar)
        self.stars = self.stars.dropna()
        self.stars = self.cut_dwarfs(self.stars)
        self.stars_temp = self.stars
        self.stars, self.files = self.match_to_filenames(self.stars)
        self.cnt = np.load("cannon_continuum_apogee.npz")

        
        self.spectrum = None
        self.mask = None
        self.error = None
        self.bitmask = None
        self.wavelength = None
        
        self.all_norm = None
        
    def save_cols(self, filename):
        allStar = pd.DataFrame()

        cols = ['FILE',
                'APSTAR_ID',
                'TARGET_ID',
                'ASPCAP_ID',
                'APOGEE_ID',
                'TEFF', 
                'LOGG',
                'FE_H', 
                'SI_FE',
                'MG_FE',
                'SNR',
                'FIELD']


        for i in cols:
            allStar[i] = fits.open(filename)[1].data[i]
        
        return allStar
    
    def cut_dwarfs(self, star):
        star_cut = star[(star['SNR'] > 50) & (star['TEFF'] < 5700) & (star['LOGG'] < 4) & (star['FE_H'] > -1)]
        return star_cut
    
    
    def get_norm_spec(self, filename, obs_num, deg = 2, verbose = False):
        """ Gets normalized spectrum when provided filename. """
        files_df = self.files
        dir_name = self.dir_name
        cnt = self.cnt
        good_i = np.where(files_df['FILE'] == filename)[0][0]
        filepath = dir_name + files_df.iloc[good_i]['FIELD'] + "/"+ files_df.iloc[good_i]['FILE']
        dat = fits.open(filepath)
        
        spectrum = dat[1].data[obs_num]
        self.spectrum = spectrum
        error = dat[2].data[obs_num]
        self.error = error
        mask = dat[3].data[obs_num]
        self.mask = mask

        CRVAL = dat[1].header['CRVAL1']
        CRDELT1 = dat[1].header['CDELT1'] 
        wavelength = 10**np.arange(CRVAL, CRVAL + len(spectrum)*CRDELT1, CRDELT1)
        self.wavelength = wavelength
        
        idx = (mask & 4351) == 0
        
        self.bitmask = idx
        #idx = ~bm.bitfield_to_boolean_mask(mask, ignore_flags = 2 ** np.array([8, 9, 10, 11, 13, 14, 15]))

        fit, pl, wav_cnt, spec_cnt, error_cnt, cnt_idx = self.normalize_spectrum(wavelength[idx], 
                                                                   spectrum[idx], 
                                                                   error[idx], 
                                                                   cnt,
                                                                   deg = deg,
                                                                   verbose = True)
        
        wpl = self.get_pl(wavelength)
        
        norm_wav = np.array([])
        norm_spec = np.array([])
        norm_error = np.array([])
        
        error[~idx] = 1e5
        
        for chip in range(3):
            norm_wav = np.hstack([norm_wav, wavelength[wpl[chip]]])
            norm_spec = np.hstack([norm_spec, spectrum[wpl[chip]] / fit[chip](wavelength[wpl[chip]])])
            norm_error = np.hstack([norm_error, error[wpl[chip]] / fit[chip](wavelength[wpl[chip]])])
        
        if verbose:
            return fit, pl, wav_cnt, spec_cnt, error_cnt, cnt_idx
        
        return norm_wav, norm_spec, norm_error
        
        
    def match_to_filenames(self, star_cut):
        def get_filenames(dir_name):
            files = [i for i in os.listdir(dir_name) if 'fits' in i]
            return files

        NGC = get_filenames(self.dir_name + "N6791/")
        NGC_field = ["N6791" for i in NGC]
        M15 = get_filenames(self.dir_name + "M15/")
        M15_field = ["M15" for i in M15]
        O60 = get_filenames(self.dir_name + "060+00")
        O60_field = ["060+00" for i in O60]
        K2 = get_filenames(self.dir_name + "K2_C4_168-21")
        K2_field = ["K2_C4_168-21" for i in K2]

        all_files = NGC + M15 + O60 + K2
        all_fields = NGC_field + M15_field + O60_field + K2_field

        files_df = pd.DataFrame(all_files, columns = ["FILE"])
        files_df['FIELD'] = all_fields
        print(len(star_cut))
        sf = star_cut.merge(files_df, on = ['FILE', 'FIELD'])
        print(len(sf))
        return sf, files_df
    
    def get_pl(self, wavelength):
        # HARDCODED CHIP WAVELENGTHS
        pl1 = wavelength < self.wav_lim1
        pl2 = (wavelength > self.wav_lim1) & (wavelength < self.wav_lim2)
        pl3 = (wavelength > self.wav_lim2)

        return pl1, pl2, pl3

    def normalize_spectrum(self, wavelength, spectrum, error, cnt, deg = 2, verbose = False):
        match_idx = np.searchsorted(wavelength, cnt['wavelengths'][cnt['trusted']])
        match_idx = match_idx[match_idx != len(wavelength)]
        wav_cnt = wavelength[match_idx]
        spec_cnt = spectrum[match_idx]
        error_cnt = error[match_idx]

        pl = self.get_pl(wav_cnt)
        fit = []

        for i in range(3):
            cbpl1 = np.polynomial.chebyshev.Chebyshev.fit(wav_cnt[pl[i]], spec_cnt[pl[i]], deg = deg, w = (1 / error_cnt[pl[i]]))
            fit.append(cbpl1)

        if verbose:
            return fit, pl, wav_cnt, spec_cnt, error_cnt, match_idx

        return fit, pl 
    
    def normalize_all_spectra(self, N):
        self.all_norm = pd.DataFrame([], columns = ["wav", "spec", "err", "FILE"])
        for f in self.stars['FILE'][:N]:
            try:
                a = list(self.get_norm_spec(f, obs_num = 0, deg = 3))
                a.append(f)
                self.all_norm = pd.concat([self.all_norm, pd.DataFrame([a], columns = ["wav", "spec", "err", "FILE"])])
            except:
                print(f)
                continue
        
        self.all_norm = self.all_norm.reset_index(drop = True)
        
        return self.all_norm

np.random.seed(80)
class Training:
    
    def __init__(self, allspec, s, frac = 0.5):
        
        self.allspec = allspec
        self.spec_class = s
        self.cols = ["TEFF", "LOGG", "FE_H", "SI_FE", "MG_FE"]
        
        
        self.allspec = self.allspec.merge(s.stars[['FILE', 'SNR'] + self.cols], on = "FILE")
        
        
        
        print(len(self.allspec))
        
        self.train, self.test = self.split_data(self.allspec, frac)
   
    def split_data(self, allspec, frac):
        N = len(allspec)
        deck = np.arange(0, N)
        np.random.shuffle(deck)
        rand_nums = deck[:int(frac * N)]
        idx = np.zeros(N).astype(bool)
        idx[rand_nums] = True
        return allspec.loc[~idx], allspec.loc[idx]
    
    def get_param_set(self):
    
        def powerset(iterable):
            "powerset([1,2,3]) --> () (1,) (2,) (3,) (1,2) (1,3) (2,3) (1,2,3)"
            s = list(iterable)
            p = list(chain.from_iterable(combinations(s, r) for r in range(len(s)+1)))
            q = [i for i in p if len(i) < 3]
            return q
        
        return powerset(self.s.stars.columns[5:10])
    
    def select_normalize_data(self, param_tab, train = False):
        p_set = param_tab[self.cols].copy()
        if train:
            self.p_mean = p_set.mean()
            self.p_std = p_set.std()
        
        p_set = (p_set - self.p_mean) / self.p_std
        return p_set

    def A(self, param_tab = None, train = False):
        if param_tab is None:
            param_tab = self.train
        
        p_set = self.select_normalize_data(param_tab, train = train)
        a = self.cols

        for i in range(len(a)):
            for j in range(len(a[i:])):
                p = a[i]
                q = a[j]
                p_set.loc[:, f"{p}_{q}"] = p_set[p] * p_set[q]

        p_set.insert(0, "CONST", 1)

        return np.array(p_set)
    
    def B(self):
        return np.array(self.train["spec"].values.tolist())
    
#     def rtwt(self):
#         return 1 / np.array(self.train["err"].values.tolist()) ** 2
    
    def wt(self):
        return np.array(self.train["SNR"])
    
        
    def diag_wt(self, train = False):
        if train:
            return np.diag(self.train["SNR"])
        else:
            return np.diag(self.test["SNR"])
    
    def solve_X(self):
#         A = (self.rtwt().T @ self.A(train = True))
#         Y = (self.rtwt().T @ self.B())
#         A = (self.A(train = True))
#         Y = (self.B())
        A = (self.diag_wt(train = True) @ self.A(train = True))
        Y = (self.diag_wt(train = True) @ self.B())
#         A = (self.wt() @ self.A(train = True))
#         Y = (self.wt() @ self.B())
        X, res, _, _ = np.linalg.lstsq(A, Y, rcond = None)
        self.X = X
        return X, res
    
    def pred_spectrum(self, param_tab):
        A_label = self.A(param_tab)
        return A_label @ self.X
    
    def train_index(self, i):
        return pd.DataFrame([self.train[self.cols].loc[i]])

class TrainingNew:
    
    def __init__(self, allspec, s, frac = 0.5):
        
        self.allspec = allspec
        self.spec_class = s
        self.cols = ["TEFF", "LOGG", "FE_H", "SI_FE", "MG_FE"]
        
        
        self.allspec = self.allspec.merge(s.stars[['FILE', 'SNR'] + self.cols], on = "FILE")
        
        
        
        print(len(self.allspec))
        
        self.train, self.test = self.split_data(self.allspec, frac)
        
        self.wt = 1 / (np.array(self.train["err"].values.tolist()) ** 2)
        self.spec = np.array(self.train["spec"].values.tolist())
        self.wav = np.array(self.train["wav"].values.tolist())
        
        
   
    def split_data(self, allspec, frac):
        N = len(allspec)
        deck = np.arange(0, N)
        np.random.shuffle(deck)
        rand_nums = deck[:int(frac * N)]
        idx = np.zeros(N).astype(bool)
        idx[rand_nums] = True
        return allspec.loc[~idx], allspec.loc[idx]
    
    def get_param_set(self):
    
        def powerset(iterable):
            "powerset([1,2,3]) --> () (1,) (2,) (3,) (1,2) (1,3) (2,3) (1,2,3)"
            s = list(iterable)
            p = list(chain.from_iterable(combinations(s, r) for r in range(len(s)+1)))
            q = [i for i in p if len(i) < 3]
            return q
        
        return powerset(self.s.stars.columns[5:10])
    
    def select_normalize_data(self, param_tab, train = False):
        p_set = param_tab[self.cols].copy()
        if train:
            self.p_mean = p_set.mean()
            self.p_std = p_set.std()
        
        #p_set = (p_set - self.p_mean) / self.p_std
        return p_set

    def A(self, param_tab = None, train = False):
        if param_tab is None:
            param_tab = self.train
        
        p_set = self.select_normalize_data(param_tab, train = train)
        a = self.cols

        for i in range(len(a)):
            for j in range(len(a[i:])):
                p = a[i]
                q = a[j]
                p_set.loc[:, f"{p}_{q}"] = p_set[p] * p_set[q]

        p_set.insert(0, "CONST", 1)

        return np.array(p_set)
    
    def B(self, i):
        return self.spec[:, i]
    
        
    def icov(self, i):
        return self.wt[:, i]
    
    def solve_X(self):
        
        A = self.A(train = True)
        X = np.zeros((A.shape[1], len(self.train.iloc[0]["spec"])))
        
        for i in range(len(self.train.iloc[0]["spec"])):
     #       for slam in np.arange(1, 110, 10):
     #           Cinv = self.icov(i) / (1 + self.icov(i) * (slam ** 2))
                Ai = A.T @ (self.icov(i)[:, None] * A)
                Yi = A.T @ (self.icov(i) *self.B(i))
                X[:, i], _, _, _ = np.linalg.lstsq(Ai, Yi, rcond = None)
      #          A @ X[:, i]
            
        self.X = X
        return X
    
    
    def pred_spectrum(self, param_tab):
        A_label = self.A(param_tab)
        return A_label.dot(self.X)
    
    def train_index(self, i):
        return pd.DataFrame([self.train[self.cols].iloc[i]])
    
    def test_index(self, i):
        return pd.DataFrame([self.train[self.cols].iloc[i]])

from scipy.optimize import curve_fit

def chisq_minimize(dummy, TEFF, LOGG, FE_H, SI_FE, MG_FE):
    param_tab = pd.DataFrame([[TEFF, LOGG, FE_H, SI_FE, MG_FE]], 
                             columns = ["TEFF", "LOGG", "FE_H", "SI_FE", "MG_FE"])
    y = t.pred_spectrum(param_tab)
    return y[0]

popt_all = pd.DataFrame([], columns = t.cols)


for i in t.test.index:
    fit_wav = t.test.loc[i]["spec"]
    fit_err = t.test.loc[i]["err"]
    try:
        popt, pcov = curve_fit(f = chisq_minimize, 
                               xdata = fit_wav, 
                               ydata = fit_wav,
                               sigma = fit_err,
                               p0 = [4605, 2.35, -0.11, 0.04, 0.08],
                               bounds = ([3200, -0.5, -1, -0.7, -0.7],
                                         [5800, 4, 0.5, 0.5, 0.5]),
                               method = 'trf')
    except RuntimeError:
        popt = np.array([np.nan, np.nan, np.nan, np.nan, np.nan])
    popt_all = pd.concat([popt_all, pd.DataFrame([popt], columns = t.cols)])

import pymc3 as pm

with pm.Model() as model:

    # Define the priors on each parameter:
    Teff = pm.Uniform("Teff", lower=4000, upper=5000)
    logg = pm.Uniform("logg", lower=1.8, upper=2.7)
    feh = pm.Uniform("feh", lower=-0.6, upper=-0.2)
    sife = pm.Uniform("sife", lower=-0.2, upper=0.4)
    mgfe = pm.Uniform("mgfe", lower =-0.2, upper = 0.4)
    logsig = pm.Uniform("logsig", lower=-10, upper=10)
    
    prm_tab = pd.DataFrame([[Teff, logg, feh, sife, mgfe]], columns = t.cols)
    
    # Define the likelihood. A few comments:
    #  1. For mathematical operations like "exp", you can't use
    #     numpy. Instead, use the mathematical operations defined
    #     in "pm.math".
    #  2. To condition on data, you use the "observed" keyword
    #     argument to any distribution. In this case, we want to
    #     use the "Normal" distribution (look up the docs for
    #     this).
    # Note sigma --> sd in pymc3.
    pm.Normal("obs", mu=t.pred_spectrum(param_tab = prm_tab)[0], 
              sigma= norm_error + pm.math.exp(logsig), observed=norm_spec)

    # This is how you will sample the model. Take a look at the
    # docs to see that other parameters that are available.
    trace = pm.sample(draws=1000, tune=1200, chains=4, cores=4)
